Afro-roots Reggae star, Olisuru Rex Ogunniyi aka Rex Suru, has opened up on how his Cherubim Vibes records berthed in California in far away the United States of America. In a recent chat with The Nation, Rex Suru said the inspiration to start the music company was divine. He said, “Years back in 1989, while working on a high-rise building in San Francisco, California, a question crossed my mind to our heavenly father, which was, ‘Father, what should I name my band?  Instantly, I heard within me, Cherubim Vibes,” he began.   Jaruma remanded after Regina Daniel’s husband petition     I suck at showing interest in people – Ex-BBNaija’s…     Sammie Okposo pulls down apology post   Suru, whose new single, ‘Good Morning Jah Jah,’ is making waves, said it was through the same divine intervention that he named his production company, House of Rhythms. “I also asked, what should I name my production company,  I also heard in reply, House of Rhythms Production. In 2018, I registered my company as Cherubim Vibes records, under which all my songs and other artists under the label are published.” With an aim to spread love and unity through music and make his Cherubim Vibes Records a beacon that will revolutionise the music industry in a positive light, Rex Suru says he has signed on two music acts, Queen  Bebra and Helena, alongside himself on the record label. - Advertisement - On what the year holds for Rex Suru, he says, “We thank God for the New Year, and hope for many more to come. We hope to spread love and unity through music and make Cherubim Vibes Records a be-con that will revolutionize the music industry in a positive light.”